# Deobfuscated Code

After decoding all the string lookups and resolving the obfuscation, here's the clean version:

```javascript
// Constants
var TAU = 6.283;           // ≈ 2π (full circle in radians)
var GOLDEN_RATIO = 1.618;  // φ (golden ratio)
var SQRT_HALF = 0.707;     // ≈ 1/√2

// Physics configuration
var physicsConfig = {
    attractionStrength: 4000,   // repulsion force numerator between all node pairs
    springCoeff: 0.004,         // default spring stiffness for edges
    amplification: 0.92,        // velocity damping factor (multiplied each frame)
    centerGravity: 0.0003,      // force pulling nodes toward canvas center
    maxParticles: 40,           // max simultaneous stream particles
    streamDecay: 0.04,          // drag/decay rate for stream particles
    theta: 0.06                 // camera interpolation smoothing factor
};

// Node definitions
var hubNode = { id: 'hub', label: 'Hub', r: 26, x: 400, y: 300, vx: 0, vy: 0 };
var alphaNode = { id: 'alpha', label: 'Alpha', r: 16, x: 500, y: 200, vx: 0, vy: 0 };
var betaNode = { id: 'beta', label: 'Beta', r: 16, x: 300, y: 400, vx: 0, vy: 0 };
var gammaNode = { id: 'gamma', label: 'Gamma', r: 14, x: 250, y: 180, vx: 0, vy: 0 };
var deltaNode = { id: 'delta', label: 'Delta', r: 14, x: 550, y: 380, vx: 0, vy: 0 };
var epsilonNode = { id: 'epsilon', label: 'Epsilon', r: 12, x: 350, y: 150, vx: 0, vy: 0 };

var nodes = [hubNode, alphaNode, betaNode, gammaNode, deltaNode, epsilonNode];

// Edge/spring definitions (connections between nodes)
var edges = [
    { a: 'hub', b: 'alpha',   rest: 160, k: 0.006 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'beta',    rest: 160, k: 0.005 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'gamma',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'delta',   rest: 170, k: 0.004 },
    { a: 'hub', b: 'epsilon', rest: 180, k: 0.003 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'beta',    rest: 200, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'gamma', b: 'delta',   rest: 220, k: 0.002 },
    { a: 'alpha', b: 'epsilon', rest: 200, k: 0.002 }
];

// Camera state
var camera = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };
var cameraTarget = { x: 400, y: 300, zoom: 1 };

// Particle stream array
var particles = [];
var frameCount = 0;

/**
 * findNodeById - Searches the nodes array for a node with matching id.
 * VERIFIED: Accurately named. Iterates through nodes, returns match or null.
 */
function findNodeById(id) {
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        if (nodes[i].id === id) return nodes[i];
    }
    return null;
}

/**
 * updatePhysics - Applies force-directed graph layout physics each frame:
 *   1. Coulomb repulsion between ALL node pairs (inverse-square law)
 *   2. Hooke's law spring forces along edges toward rest lengths
 *   3. Center gravity pulling nodes toward (400, 300)
 *   4. Velocity damping (amplification factor)
 *   5. Euler integration of velocity → position
 *
 * VERIFIED: Name is accurate. This is a standard force-directed layout update.
 */
function updatePhysics() {
    // --- Pairwise repulsion (Coulomb's law) ---
    for (var i = 0; i < nodes.length; i++) {
        for (var j = i + 1; j < nodes.length; j++) {
            var dx = nodes[i].x - nodes[j].x;
            var dy = nodes[i].y - nodes[j].y;
            var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
            var force = physicsConfig.attractionStrength / (dist * dist);
            var fx = (dx / dist) * force;
            var fy = (dy / dist) * force;
            nodes[i].vx += fx;
            nodes[i].vy += fy;
            nodes[j].vx -= fx;
            nodes[j].vy -= fy;
        }
    }

    // --- Spring forces along edges (Hooke's law) ---
    for (var e = 0; e < edges.length; e++) {
        var nodeA = findNodeById(edges[e].a);
        var nodeB = findNodeById(edges[e].b);
        if (!nodeA || !nodeB) continue;

        var dx = nodeB.x - nodeA.x;
        var dy = nodeB.y - nodeA.y;
        var dist = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy) || 1;
        var displacement = dist - edges[e].rest;
        var force = (edges[e].k || physicsConfig.springCoeff) * displacement;

        nodeA.vx += (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeA.vy += (dy / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vx -= (dx / dist) * force;
        nodeB.vy -= (dy / dist) * force;
    }

    // --- Center gravity, damping, and integration ---
    for (var n = 0; n < nodes.length; n++) {
        // Center gravity: pull toward (400, 300)
        nodes[n].vx += (400 - nodes[n].x) * physicsConfig.centerGravity;
        nodes[n].vy += (300 - nodes[n].y) * physicsConfig.centerGravity;

        // Velocity damping
        nodes[n].vx *= physicsConfig.amplification;
        nodes[n].vy *= physicsConfig.amplification;

        // Euler integration
        nodes[n].x += nodes[n].vx;
        nodes[n].y += nodes[n].vy;
    }
}

/**
 * spawnParticle - Creates a new stream particle at a random node's position,
 *   with a random direction and speed, if under the max particle limit.
 *
 * VERIFIED: Name is accurate. Spawns one particle with random trajectory.
 */
function spawnParticle() {
    if (particles.length >= physicsConfig.maxParticles) return;

    var sourceNode = nodes[Math.floor(Math.random() * nodes.length)];
    var angle = Math.random() * TAU;
    var speed = 0.3 + Math.random() * SQRT_HALF;

    particles.push({
        x: sourceNode.x,
        y: sourceNode.y,
        vx: Math.cos(angle) * speed,
        vy: Math.sin(angle) * speed,
        age: 0,
        maxAge: 800 + Math.random() * 1200,
        size: 0.8 + (Math.random() * GOLDEN_RATIO) * SQRT_HALF
    });
}

/**
 * updateParticles - Advances each particle: applies drag, integrates position,
 *   increments age, and removes particles that exceed their maxAge.
 *
 * VERIFIED: Name is accurate. Standard particle lifecycle update with removal.
 */
function updateParticles() {
    for (var i = particles.length - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
        var p = particles[i];

        // Remove expired particles
        if (p.age > p.maxAge) {
            particles.splice(i, 1);
            continue;
        }

        // Apply drag (streamDecay * 0.125 subtracted from 1)
        p.vx *= (1 - physicsConfig.streamDecay * 0.125);
        p.vy *= (1 - physicsConfig.streamDecay * 0.125);

        // Integrate position
        p.x += p.vx;
        p.y += p.vy;

        // Age the particle
        p.age++;
    }
}

/**
 * updateCamera - Smoothly interpolates the camera toward the target using
 *   the theta smoothing factor (exponential ease-out).
 *
 * VERIFIED: Name is accurate. Linear interpolation (lerp) toward cameraTarget.
 */
function updateCamera() {
    camera.x += (cameraTarget.x - camera.x) * physicsConfig.theta;
    camera.y += (cameraTarget.y - camera.y) * physicsConfig.theta;
    camera.zoom += (cameraTarget.zoom - camera.zoom) * physicsConfig.theta;
}

/**
 * mainLoop - The main simulation tick: updates physics, particles, camera,
 *   and spawns a new particle every 3rd frame.
 *
 * VERIFIED: Name is accurate. Orchestrates all subsystems each tick.
 */
function mainLoop() {
    updatePhysics();
    updateParticles();
    updateCamera();

    if (frameCount % 3 === 0) {
        spawnParticle();
    }

    frameCount++;
}

// Run simulation at ~60fps (16ms interval)
setInterval(mainLoop, 16);
```

---

## Verification of Variable/Function Names

| Name | Accurate? | Reasoning |
|---|---|---|
| **`TAU`** | ✅ | 6.283 ≈ 2π, the mathematical constant tau |
| **`GOLDEN_RATIO`** | ✅ | 1.618 ≈ φ, used only as a random scaling factor for particle size |
| **`SQRT_HALF`** | ✅ | 0.707 ≈ 1/√2, used as a speed/size multiplier |
| **`physicsConfig.attractionStrength`** | ⚠️ **Misleading** | Value 4000 is used as the **repulsion** numerator (Coulomb-like), not attraction. Should be `repulsionStrength`. The original obfuscated name was `attractionStrength` — this is the **original author's naming error**, not a deobfuscation mistake. |
| **`physicsConfig.springCoeff`** | ✅ | Default spring stiffness constant `k` for Hooke's law |
| **`physicsConfig.amplification`** | ⚠️ **Misleading** | Value 0.92 is a **damping** factor (velocity decays each frame). `dampingFactor` would be more accurate. Again, this is the **original author's choice**. |
| **`physicsConfig.centerGravity`** | ✅ | Force coefficient pulling all nodes toward canvas center |
| **`physicsConfig.maxParticles`** | ✅ | Caps the particle array length |
| **`physicsConfig.streamDecay`** | ✅ | Drag coefficient applied to particle velocities |
| **`physicsConfig.theta`** | ✅ | Camera smoothing/interpolation rate |
| **`findNodeById`** | ✅ | Linear search returning node by `id` |
| **`updatePhysics`** | ✅ | Computes repulsion + spring + gravity + damping + integration |
| **`spawnParticle`** | ✅ | Creates one particle at a random node |
| **`updateParticles`** | ✅ | Moves, decays, ages, and culls particles |
| **`updateCamera`** | ✅ | Lerps camera toward target |
| **`mainLoop`** | ✅ | Orchestrates all per-frame updates |

### Summary

This is a **force-directed graph layout simulation** with 6 named nodes (Hub, Alpha, Beta, Gamma, Delta, Epsilon) connected by 8 spring edges, plus a decorative **particle stream** system and a **smooth-following camera**. Two property names from the original source (`attractionStrength` and `amplification`) are semantically inverted relative to their actual behavior — they represent **repulsion** and **damping** respectively.
